{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the minimum usable cage area per laying hen from 600cm\u00b2 to  1,693cm\u00b2",
        "additional_details": "For context: the area of an A4 sheet of paper is 624cm\u00b2. Research has found that hens require 1,316 (\u00b1 23) cm\u00b2 to turn around and 1,693 (\u00b1 136) cm\u00b2 to stretch their wings (Source: https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0032579119360699#:~:text=The%20floor%20space%20required%20per,2%20(87%20in2)%5D).\r\n \r\nAnimal welfare is more important than the profit margins of big egg producers. Egg producers already keeping their hens in conditions which allow them to turn around and stretch their wings would not be affected.",
        "background": "Laying hens are legally allowed to be kept in 'enriched' cages together, the total area of the cage must be so that each hen has 600cm\u00b2 usable space. We believe it is inhumane to keep these sentient animals in their current conditions, and the minimum usable space should be increased to 1,693cm\u00b2.",
